Step-by-step reasoning:
- The user wants to turn off the Kitchen Lights when the Thermostat mode changes to Off.
- This is a COS condition checking the Thermostat's Mode property equals Off (value 0).
- The action is to send the Off command (DOF) to the Kitchen Lights device.
- No nested if blocks; single condition and action.

{
  "routine": {
    "name": "Turn off Kitchen Lights when Thermostat is Off",
    "condition": {
      "==": {
        "device": "n007_c0a801b6",
        "status": "Mode",
        "value": 0,
        "uom": "enum",
        "precision": 0
      }
    },
    "action": {
      "device": "49 6C 5F 1",
      "command": "DOF",
      "parameters": []
    }
  }
}
